data.text:
May 11, 1980 was a Sunday and it was the 132nd day of the year 1980 in the Gregorian calendar.

May 11, 1980 can also be written as 5/11/1980 in the US and as 11/5/1980 in UK and Europe.

The Zodiac and Astrological sign for May 11th is Taurus.

Taurus is the 2nd sign in the Western Zodiac. People born between April 20th and May 20th belong to the Taurus sign: discover Taurus personality and who should a Taurus marry.

Babies born in May are either Taurus or Gemini. People born before May 20th are Taurus, while people born from May 21st have the sign of Gemini.

Moon phase

The moon phase on May 11, 1980 was Waning crescent.

The moon phase refers to the appearance of the Moon in the night sky on May 11, 1980 and is determined by the portion of the Moon's illuminated surface that is visible from Earth.

An observer located in New York City on May 11, 1980 at 10pm, would see the moon, being 3% full, rising at 04:11 am and setting at 05:56 pm.

The previous full moon was on Apr 30, 1980 while the next full moon would come on May 29, 1980.

What is special about May 11th?

May 11th refers to a specific date on the calendar, which is the 11th day of the month of May. It is a date that occurs annually and is part of the Gregorian calendar, which is widely used around the world.

Over the years several events happened on May 11th, such as:

2019 - Yemeni civil war (2015-present). houthi forces begin to pull out of several yemeni ports including al hudaydah and as-salif. this withdrawal is part of an un-brokered ceasefire agreement that aims at ending the yemeni blockade.

2018 - After six weeks of protests, the israel defense forces open fire again with tear gas and live bullets on palestinian protestors. one person has been killed, and 146 more are injured. some protestors also throw stones and burn tires.

2017 - Battle of mosul: lt gen othman al-ghanmi (iraqi army chief of staff) states that his security forces are just days away from completing operation recapture mosul from isil.
